==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Taciturnity
<hw>Tac`i*tur"ni*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>taciturnitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>taciturnit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Habitual silence, or reserve in speaking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The cause of Addison's <qex>taciturnity</qex> was a natural
diffidence in the company of strangers.</q> <rj><qau>V.
Knox.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>taciturnity</qex> and the short answers which gave so
much offense.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tack</ent>⟦br⟧
